==Abstract==

This IIP introduces the "feefilter" message to inform peers of the minimum fee rate for transaction relay. It is adapted from BIP 133 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Nodes have different minimum relay fee policies. Broadcasting low-fee transactions to nodes that will reject them wastes bandwidth. The feefilter message allows nodes to communicate their policies.

==Specification==

===feefilter Message===

<pre>
feefilter:
  feerate: uint64   // Minimum fee rate in int/kvB
</pre>

===Behavior===

After sending feefilter, a node SHOULD NOT send inv messages for transactions below the specified fee rate.

The fee rate is expressed in int per 1000 virtual bytes (int/kvB).

===Updates===

Nodes MAY send updated feefilter messages as mempool conditions change.

===Calculation===

<pre>
feerate = (tx_fee * 1000) / tx_vsize
</pre>

Where tx_vsize is the transaction's virtual size.

